The defendant Aaron Berzowski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Aaron Berzowski is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

Original Transcript (65 pages) commencing on 07-14-2014 CHANGE OF PLEA AND SENTENCING HEARING received and filed.

Certification of transcript of proceedings of a PRELIMINARY HEARING commencing on 04-11-2014 received and filed. (34 Pages.)
Copy of transcript forwarded to ATTORNEY JOHN GLOVER.

Defendant Aaron Berzowski in court with attorney John C. Glover.  Defendant Aaron Berzowski in custody.  Randy P. Sitzberger appeared for the State of Wisconsin./ SAB
Defense withdrew their previously filed motion to suppress. 
AS TO COUNTS 1 and 3:
Pursuant to Plea negotiations, Court ordered Counts 1 and 3 DISMISSED.
AS TO COUNT 2:
  Defendant  advised that if he/she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.   Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. 
  Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by the State, defense counsel and defendant. Additional statements by: Johnikka N.
The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 5 YEARS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 1 YEAR and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 4 YEARS, consecutive to any other sentence, credit for 105 days.
Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
-Restitution set at zero
-Court costs and victim/witness surcharges are to be collected by DOC from up to 25% of prison funds, balance to be paid by 7/14/2019; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment.
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge  to be collected by DOC from up to 25% of prison funds, balance to be paid by 7/14/2019; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment.
CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers
-No alcohol or controlled substances
-Mental health assessment and any recommended treatment to include any couseling, therapy and taking any prescribed medications
-Employment or school
-Successfully complete a Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Modification Program
Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon he may no longer use or possess any firearms or body armor; also he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been restored.
